1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
Now you just pretend you hadn't talked to me any before, and you tell me about the government moving you up here.

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:12,000
Well, now, I don't remember the day or the month or nothing like that, you understand?

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:19,000
But I know they come one evening, and I just was fixing to quit working in my garden.

4
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:27,000
And he comes and he says, well, says, is this Miss Davis?

5
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,000
And I said, that's what they call me.

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:39,580
other words ain't loose, I suggest. He says, well, I'm taking pictures around, says the

7
00:00:39,580 --> 00:00:50,060
government's gonna take over everything and Gainesville's gonna have to move out. I said, all this many years? I said, you talk crazy.

8
00:00:50,060 --> 00:01:00,060
And he's like, he says, no. Says, I'm here just to tell you. He says, put me to work.

9
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:08,000
And he says, uh, then my chickens was all out and it was late in the evening, you know.

10
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:17,000
I told him, I says, well you'll have to excuse me, I got to put my chickens in the chicken yard.

11
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,000
He says, that's just what I want you to do.

12
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Well, there was a shark fellow with him, you know.

13
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:26,000
But he didn't ever tell me who he was, you understand?

14
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
And I went to put my chickens in the chicken yard.

15
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:36,640
and fed them, and I had on my old bonnet and shirt where I'd been working, you know, and I

16
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:43,680
throwed the corn out, and I noticed this short feller walked up close to him and said something

17
00:01:43,680 --> 00:01:49,200
I noticed, and he said, well, you've got a pretty bunch of chickens, says, do they lay?

18
00:01:50,160 --> 00:01:55,920
I says, yes. I said, sometimes I pick up nine eggs a day and sometimes I don't.

19
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:59,920
He said, well, this sure is a pretty fellow.

20
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:07,080
Well, I didn't know this shark man walked up to him and took my picture just as I went

21
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:10,080
to throw some corn out to him, you know.
